WEBVTT

00:00:01.120 --> 00:00:03.950
"Everyone must have someone
they want to kill."</i>

00:00:04.230 --> 00:00:06.540
l think this is what started it.</i>

00:00:06.780 --> 00:00:10.980
We wrote the name of the person
we want to kill half-jokingly,</i>

00:00:11.260 --> 00:00:13.040
"Asao Hosokawa"
<i>and secretly showed each other.</i>

00:00:15.220 --> 00:00:16.420
Right after that...</i>

00:00:17.260 --> 00:00:19.620
The name l wrote was
Yutaro Yamagiwa.</i>

00:00:21.340 --> 00:00:24.180
People are murdered
one after next...</i>

00:00:24.260 --> 00:00:25.100
"Masao Tanaka"

00:00:25.180 --> 00:00:28.900
They said he got a note that says,
"lt is your turn to kill!"

00:00:29.220 --> 00:00:31.180
People are cornered...</i>

00:00:31.300 --> 00:00:33.460
The name l wrote
on my piece of paper

00:00:33.820 --> 00:00:35.860
was Misato Akaike.

00:00:36.140 --> 00:00:39.340
I heard you played a dangerous
game at the residents' meeting.

00:00:39.460 --> 00:00:40.340
You knew?

00:00:41.220 --> 00:00:43.900
I think we should tell the police
about the game.

00:00:43.980 --> 00:00:44.820
But still...</i>

00:00:44.900 --> 00:00:47.580
Maybe we would all be treated
as a murderer for a while.

00:00:47.660 --> 00:00:50.660
I did nothing, so l don't want to be
treated as an accomplice!

00:00:50.740 --> 00:00:52.780
We didn't talk to the police...</i>

00:00:52.860 --> 00:00:57.100
l wrote on the ballot paper that
l wanted to kill Yoshihiko Hakamada.

00:00:58.260 --> 00:00:59.820
And one more person died.</i>

00:01:05.740 --> 00:01:08.150
"Yoshihiko Hakamada"

00:01:10.130 --> 00:01:13.450
"Episode 6"

00:01:15.210 --> 00:01:16.810
Don't panic, loser.

00:01:17.130 --> 00:01:18.130
Sorry.

00:01:22.900 --> 00:01:23.900
Also,

00:01:24.100 --> 00:01:26.020
that isn't the only problem.

00:01:28.380 --> 00:01:29.340
Thank you.

00:01:48.310 --> 00:01:49.150
Big Bro.

00:01:49.550 --> 00:01:50.630
You startled me...

00:01:50.870 --> 00:01:51.790
What's the matter?

00:01:52.510 --> 00:01:53.750
I saw you.

00:01:55.510 --> 00:01:57.150
You went to meet Nana, right?

00:02:00.230 --> 00:02:01.070
Calm down.

00:02:01.750 --> 00:02:04.430
Anyway, when did you know her?

00:02:05.430 --> 00:02:06.350
You hit on her?

00:02:06.710 --> 00:02:08.820
But you're married, right?

00:02:09.940 --> 00:02:11.180
Yeah...

00:02:11.260 --> 00:02:14.420
Well, Nana is pretty,

00:02:15.020 --> 00:02:19.820
so l can understand why
you want to make a move on her.

00:02:20.300 --> 00:02:21.390
But you shouldn't.

00:02:22.190 --> 00:02:24.870
Nana is my wife!

00:02:26.270 --> 00:02:28.110
Oh, is she?

00:02:28.470 --> 00:02:34.430
Well, l am happy that
my wife is popular,

00:02:35.230 --> 00:02:38.150
but l had no idea that you...

00:02:38.510 --> 00:02:40.510
l think we do get along, right?

00:02:40.590 --> 00:02:43.110
We even have the same taste
in women! The same!

00:02:44.390 --> 00:02:46.670
Your wife is popular,
doesn't it worry you?

00:02:46.750 --> 00:02:48.990
One worries because
he hasn't had enough training.

00:02:49.070 --> 00:02:50.390
It's a different matter.

00:02:50.470 --> 00:02:52.270
No, it's image training.

00:02:52.670 --> 00:02:58.950
"If my beloved wife has an affair."
That's the image training l do.

00:02:59.470 --> 00:03:03.870
In the end, my plan is to love
Nana more than anyone else.

00:03:04.030 --> 00:03:05.390
It's the only one l have.

00:03:05.510 --> 00:03:06.350
What the heck?

00:03:06.590 --> 00:03:09.870
Even if you're serious about
pursuing Nana,

00:03:10.270 --> 00:03:14.310
l'll just give her even more love
than you do.

00:03:15.430 --> 00:03:18.180
We worked together for a while,

00:03:19.300 --> 00:03:20.940
then we met again after a long time.

00:03:21.100 --> 00:03:23.590
I had no idea
that she was your wife.

00:03:25.150 --> 00:03:28.230
What? "l had no idea"?

00:03:28.670 --> 00:03:29.510
What?

00:03:29.630 --> 00:03:32.910
It should be,
"l had no idea, sorry," right?

00:03:34.310 --> 00:03:35.150
Sorry.

00:03:35.670 --> 00:03:37.590
Okay, we're friends again.

00:03:43.470 --> 00:03:45.630
We'll give you the latest update
on the case.</i>

00:03:45.750 --> 00:03:49.270
In 1991, when Mr Yoshihiko Hakamada
was 18 years old,</i>

00:03:49.350 --> 00:03:52.110
he won the Junon Super Boy Contest
Grand Prix Award...</i>

00:03:52.190 --> 00:03:56.030
When l was slim,
people said l looked quite like him.

00:03:56.710 --> 00:03:58.750
I think l've seen him somewhere.

00:03:58.830 --> 00:04:01.790
Hey, it's Yoshihiko Hakamada!
You don't know him?

00:04:01.870 --> 00:04:03.390
That's not what l mean.

00:04:05.310 --> 00:04:06.230
Look, it's him!

00:04:06.310 --> 00:04:07.140
"101 Yuzuru Kuzumi"

00:04:07.220 --> 00:04:09.120
He looks like him...

00:04:09.240 --> 00:04:11.000
Wait, it's that condo again?

00:04:12.360 --> 00:04:15.720
Well, we'll concentrate on our case.

00:04:16.120 --> 00:04:18.200
"Murder of Kuramae Condo's Couple"
What's your current recommendation?

00:04:18.280 --> 00:04:19.640
"Recommendation"?

00:04:20.960 --> 00:04:22.080
This guy, l think.

00:04:22.200 --> 00:04:23.760
I still can't verify his alibi

00:04:23.840 --> 00:04:25.890
on the night
Mr and Mrs Akaike were killed.

00:04:26.650 --> 00:04:30.520
"Room 203, Xinyi Lin,
student from China"

00:05:14.030 --> 00:05:17.030
"Your Turn to Kill"

00:05:30.300 --> 00:05:32.460
lt isn't your fault, Mr Kuzumi.

00:05:33.580 --> 00:05:35.580
lt's obviously my fault.

00:05:36.460 --> 00:05:39.670
It's because l wrote
Yoshihiko Hakamada.

00:05:40.510 --> 00:05:42.430
I kept wishing him dead,

00:05:42.710 --> 00:05:46.480
but l actually think that
he's a very good actor.

00:05:47.400 --> 00:05:49.200
I think he was a good actor.

00:05:50.040 --> 00:05:52.680
Who drew your ballot paper?

00:05:53.160 --> 00:05:55.320
Yoshihiko Hakamada was a good actor!

00:05:56.000 --> 00:05:57.000
Mr Kuzumi.

00:05:59.200 --> 00:06:00.120
I'm sorry.

00:06:01.760 --> 00:06:04.760
Are you threatened by anyone?

00:06:05.600 --> 00:06:06.440
What?

00:06:06.680 --> 00:06:08.840
LIke when Mr Fujii was threatened.

00:06:09.360 --> 00:06:11.200
No, l haven't received any notes.

00:06:11.960 --> 00:06:15.240
Moreover, l don't know the man
whose name was on my paper,

00:06:15.320 --> 00:06:16.400
so how can l kill him?

00:06:17.400 --> 00:06:21.600
Will you show me
the piece of paper again?

00:06:22.240 --> 00:06:23.120
Sure.

00:06:24.400 --> 00:06:27.720
It's "Asao Hosokawa", l presume?

00:06:28.240 --> 00:06:30.440
Yes, the first name is Asao.

00:06:31.880 --> 00:06:32.720
Yes?

00:06:33.720 --> 00:06:36.520
I wrote the name.

00:06:37.240 --> 00:06:38.240
What?

00:06:38.480 --> 00:06:40.670
So, please, don't kill him.

00:06:41.230 --> 00:06:44.960
If anyone threatens you,
please talk to me.

00:06:49.320 --> 00:06:50.240
Mr Kuzumi?

00:06:51.520 --> 00:06:55.680
All of these aren't a trap you set,
right? Or are they?

00:06:56.640 --> 00:07:00.240
Suddenly, people started dying
the day you moved here.

00:07:00.920 --> 00:07:05.000
The property manager died
on the very same day you came.

00:07:06.240 --> 00:07:07.320
I am home!

00:07:09.120 --> 00:07:10.040
I'm home...

00:07:11.840 --> 00:07:14.080
Oh? Mr Kuzumi? What's the matter?

00:07:15.560 --> 00:07:16.640
You hit on her?

00:07:17.040 --> 00:07:17.880
What?

00:07:17.960 --> 00:07:20.280
No, we're talking about the game.

00:07:20.640 --> 00:07:22.560
Oh... The murder-swap.

00:07:43.680 --> 00:07:47.320
They obviously are going to
make a deal with someone.

00:07:47.680 --> 00:07:49.960
What did they carry here?

00:07:52.240 --> 00:07:53.560
Someone is here.

00:08:03.800 --> 00:08:05.120
What is going on?

00:08:07.760 --> 00:08:09.160
"Asao Hosokawa"
Wait a minute.

00:08:09.440 --> 00:08:11.320
I am this man's trainer!

00:08:12.440 --> 00:08:13.640
He told me.

00:08:13.960 --> 00:08:18.360
Big Bro will be shocked
if he's killed for hitting on you.

00:08:19.000 --> 00:08:19.840
Hit on me?

00:08:20.200 --> 00:08:21.640
That's how you knew him, right?

00:08:24.680 --> 00:08:25.520
No?

00:08:27.240 --> 00:08:29.360
- I...
- Wait... l'll guess.

00:08:29.560 --> 00:08:31.520
Orangutan Time.

00:08:32.000 --> 00:08:33.480
Nana, you're actually...

00:08:33.560 --> 00:08:34.720
Married.

00:08:36.990 --> 00:08:37.960
To him.

00:08:39.920 --> 00:08:40.760
What?

00:08:41.880 --> 00:08:42.960
I am sorry.

00:08:44.200 --> 00:08:47.480
Sorry, l don't get it at all.

00:08:47.640 --> 00:08:51.200
Who is married to whom?

00:08:51.880 --> 00:08:54.920
You've asked me to
register our marriage many times,

00:08:55.040 --> 00:08:57.000
but l still haven't, right?

00:08:57.840 --> 00:08:59.000
Because l can't.

00:08:59.520 --> 00:09:02.360
I'm still married to him
on the marriage records.

00:09:16.910 --> 00:09:18.750
Should l leave you two alone?

00:09:18.830 --> 00:09:20.550
No! Please stay here.

00:09:20.990 --> 00:09:24.070
I... I'm a bit upset
if no one else is here.

00:09:24.590 --> 00:09:25.550
Wait, but...

00:09:26.070 --> 00:09:27.710
May l hold your hand?

00:09:32.000 --> 00:09:33.310
Go on.

00:09:34.270 --> 00:09:36.680
I think l told you
that l was divorced,

00:09:37.520 --> 00:09:40.640
and that my ex-husband is Mr Hosokawa.

00:09:41.760 --> 00:09:44.560
He's the managing director
of my previous design company

00:09:45.080 --> 00:09:46.520
and he was a nice man.

00:09:47.000 --> 00:09:49.160
But many things happened
after we got married,

00:09:49.640 --> 00:09:51.920
- so we decided to get divorced.
- Many things?

00:09:52.560 --> 00:09:55.520
Sorry, may l finish this first?

00:09:55.760 --> 00:09:58.120
Yeah... Go ahead.

00:09:58.880 --> 00:10:01.520
There was one thing that
l could never forgive him for...

00:10:01.640 --> 00:10:03.840
ls it many or just one?

00:10:05.080 --> 00:10:07.160
Sorry... I'm listening.

00:10:07.800 --> 00:10:09.600
We decided to get divorced,

00:10:10.360 --> 00:10:13.800
but he said
he didn't want to see me,

00:10:14.240 --> 00:10:16.920
and asked me to post him
the divorce form.

00:10:17.080 --> 00:10:20.280
So l did what he asked
and let him submit the form.

00:10:21.200 --> 00:10:24.800
Then, when l went to
renew my driver's licence,

00:10:25.880 --> 00:10:29.350
l found out that
the form wasn't submitted.

00:10:30.310 --> 00:10:32.000
Did you tell Big Bro?

00:10:33.120 --> 00:10:35.000
I told him over and over again,

00:10:35.760 --> 00:10:38.560
but he made up excuses every time
and avoided the topic.

00:10:39.080 --> 00:10:42.040
Shota, after you proposed to me,

00:10:42.280 --> 00:10:44.440
l told him that
l wanted to marry someone.

00:10:44.680 --> 00:10:47.280
He accepted it at the time,

00:10:47.920 --> 00:10:50.160
but he still didn't submit the form.

00:10:52.560 --> 00:10:55.320
Of course,
it was partly my fault too.

00:10:56.680 --> 00:10:58.320
After l started working freelance,

00:10:58.640 --> 00:11:01.040
l still took jobs from his company.

00:11:01.400 --> 00:11:03.640
So when l think
about our future life,

00:11:04.120 --> 00:11:06.120
l just couldn't insist.

00:11:07.080 --> 00:11:08.070
Ouch! lt hurts.

00:11:10.310 --> 00:11:13.170
I am sorry!
l know they are all excuses.

00:11:17.880 --> 00:11:19.080
Yes!

00:11:19.720 --> 00:11:21.890
- It's a bull's eye!
- Yes?

00:11:22.130 --> 00:11:25.390
It's been a while since l hit
the bull's eye at Orangutan Time!

00:11:26.150 --> 00:11:26.990
What is it?

00:11:27.070 --> 00:11:30.360
I was just going to say it.

00:11:30.880 --> 00:11:35.400
Your ex-husband is actually Big Bro,

00:11:35.640 --> 00:11:38.240
and you wrote his name!

00:11:39.600 --> 00:11:41.640
Yes! l guessed it right.

00:11:43.280 --> 00:11:44.400
Shota...

00:11:45.800 --> 00:11:46.720
Sorry.

00:11:47.160 --> 00:11:48.720
Shota, don't apologise.

00:11:49.120 --> 00:11:52.040
You've been worrying about
something so serious,

00:11:52.320 --> 00:11:54.280
but l had absolutely no idea.

00:11:55.440 --> 00:11:56.520
I'll kneel.

00:11:57.040 --> 00:12:02.230
I hurt my semitendinosus a bit
during training today,

00:12:02.790 --> 00:12:04.910
so l will just bow.

00:12:06.510 --> 00:12:07.430
I am sorry.

00:12:09.670 --> 00:12:11.110
I am really sorry.

00:12:12.830 --> 00:12:14.700
- So, Mr Kuzumi.
- Yes?

00:12:15.500 --> 00:12:18.500
Please don't kill this man
by mistake!

00:12:19.700 --> 00:12:22.740
Nana had loved him so much
that she was married to him once.

00:12:23.700 --> 00:12:26.060
I won't kill him, so may l go now?

00:12:59.530 --> 00:13:02.850
"lt is your turn to kill"

00:13:03.130 --> 00:13:04.610
lt has come already?

00:13:08.100 --> 00:13:09.380
"Obey the rules properly"

00:13:12.060 --> 00:13:14.900
l met him the other day

00:13:15.580 --> 00:13:18.140
because l didn't know
who drew my piece of paper.

00:13:18.780 --> 00:13:22.460
I just wanted to see if he was
attacked or harassed in any way.

00:13:22.700 --> 00:13:23.940
I understand now.

00:13:24.700 --> 00:13:25.660
So we're all good.

00:13:28.260 --> 00:13:31.740
Anyway, is anything else
worrying you?

00:13:31.820 --> 00:13:33.850
You might as well
tell me everything now.

00:13:37.050 --> 00:13:38.090
"Room 302's occupant"

00:13:38.170 --> 00:13:40.380
l think you might be killed.

00:13:41.340 --> 00:13:45.860
Telling him more might
turn my worries into reality,</i>

00:13:46.300 --> 00:13:47.900
so l couldn't say it.</i>

00:13:48.500 --> 00:13:49.380
It's fine.

00:13:52.380 --> 00:13:53.220
I see.

00:13:53.580 --> 00:13:55.660
Let's start from doing what we can.

00:13:56.380 --> 00:13:58.540
Is there anyone you can talk to?

00:14:03.980 --> 00:14:04.940
Excuse me.

00:14:06.100 --> 00:14:08.820
Oh, detectives.
What's the matter today?

00:14:09.300 --> 00:14:10.780
We'd like to talk to her.

00:14:11.860 --> 00:14:12.740
Me?

00:14:12.940 --> 00:14:17.490
Actually, Miss Seno's fingerprints
were left in the late Akaikes' flat.

00:14:22.580 --> 00:14:24.120
Well, we have done some digging.

00:14:24.880 --> 00:14:28.000
You brought the old lady home
when she fell from her wheelchair?

00:14:29.720 --> 00:14:30.560
Yes.

00:14:30.640 --> 00:14:36.210
So, where were kind Miss Seno
and the two gentlemen on that night?

00:14:36.780 --> 00:14:38.220
The three of us went for...

00:14:38.300 --> 00:14:39.460
- a car trip.
- Dinner.

00:14:39.820 --> 00:14:41.590
Oh? Which one?

00:14:43.710 --> 00:14:45.990
We took a drive and had dinner.

00:14:47.150 --> 00:14:49.630
I see. Okay, then.

00:14:57.210 --> 00:14:59.950
"Kojima Kids English Class"

00:15:32.470 --> 00:15:33.350
Mr Ukita.

00:15:37.470 --> 00:15:39.110
Should we worry about the police?

00:15:40.710 --> 00:15:41.910
I'll take care of this.

00:15:43.610 --> 00:15:45.370
Sorry for making you do this for us.

00:15:45.770 --> 00:15:49.130
I don't do this for you two,
it's just for Airi.

00:15:50.370 --> 00:15:53.420
No, it isn't even for Airi either.

00:15:55.180 --> 00:15:58.740
It's for the promise l made
to her late mother.

00:16:01.100 --> 00:16:03.460
I won't let Airi have
a criminal record.

00:16:05.580 --> 00:16:07.300
And you should
pull yourself together.

00:16:07.700 --> 00:16:08.980
You'll marry her, right?

00:16:09.660 --> 00:16:11.500
Yes. l am sorry.

00:16:20.140 --> 00:16:23.140
When will you be back next time?
Tell me!

00:16:24.300 --> 00:16:27.020
You haven't been back for so long,
and you'll just leave now?

00:16:27.100 --> 00:16:29.340
You told me to leave
in the first place.

00:16:30.700 --> 00:16:31.540
Right?

00:16:34.860 --> 00:16:36.620
What are you doing?

00:16:39.060 --> 00:16:40.180
You're crazy.

00:16:42.180 --> 00:16:43.460
What... Hey!

00:16:44.940 --> 00:16:46.140
Trying to kill me?

00:16:46.260 --> 00:16:47.500
I want children!

00:16:47.620 --> 00:16:49.340
What? Whose?

00:16:49.500 --> 00:16:50.940
Between us!

00:16:51.060 --> 00:16:52.660
It's too late to ask me.

00:16:52.780 --> 00:16:54.260
Let's start over again.

00:16:54.740 --> 00:16:56.900
You know that isn't the problem,
don't you?

00:16:56.980 --> 00:16:57.900
We can go back!

00:16:58.180 --> 00:17:01.300
If we have children, we can go back
to the happy days...

00:17:03.060 --> 00:17:04.620
You're out of your mind.

00:17:30.420 --> 00:17:32.460
- I'll race you.
- No.

00:17:32.580 --> 00:17:35.850
- Why?
- Because you run faster than me.

00:17:36.330 --> 00:17:37.620
All right, then.

00:17:37.700 --> 00:17:39.660
l'll start two seconds later.

00:17:39.740 --> 00:17:40.700
Two seconds?

00:17:41.140 --> 00:17:43.340
Fumi, Kazu.

00:17:43.620 --> 00:17:46.700
I made Bavarois. Let's have it.

00:17:48.660 --> 00:17:50.220
I am already full.

00:17:51.260 --> 00:17:53.740
Then, Kazu, let's have it.

00:17:54.020 --> 00:17:55.140
- Ouch!
- Come with me.

00:17:55.580 --> 00:17:57.260
It hurts! Let go of me!

00:17:57.620 --> 00:17:58.500
Mummy!

00:17:58.580 --> 00:17:59.660
Come with me!

00:18:00.620 --> 00:18:02.660
Hey, what are you doing?

00:18:02.740 --> 00:18:03.660
No!

00:18:10.940 --> 00:18:11.980
Stay here.

00:18:14.980 --> 00:18:15.860
You...

00:18:15.940 --> 00:18:16.940
Why?

00:18:17.300 --> 00:18:21.140
Why am l always the lonely one?

00:18:41.300 --> 00:18:42.850
Why are you all here so late?

00:18:43.650 --> 00:18:45.770
We want to talk about the game.

00:18:49.450 --> 00:18:50.710
Let's talk somewhere else.

00:18:50.910 --> 00:18:52.690
What do you do that for?

00:18:53.690 --> 00:18:59.850
If we all know what name each person
wrote and who drew it,

00:19:00.370 --> 00:19:04.490
then maybe we can prevent
more murders from happening.

00:19:04.930 --> 00:19:09.210
Although I'm not convinced that
none of you want to tell the police,

00:19:09.330 --> 00:19:10.450
l can understand.

00:19:10.810 --> 00:19:12.610
If anyone dies because of the game,

00:19:12.730 --> 00:19:16.090
it's possible that everyone
participated is just as guilty.

