I am sorry.

00:37:47.120 --> 00:37:49.580
I didn't expect you
to delay a beat here.

00:37:49.940 --> 00:37:53.360
If you don't mind, would you tell me
how you plan to act?

00:37:55.120 --> 00:37:57.340
He said he wanted to break up
and l was hurt...

00:37:57.420 --> 00:38:00.130
But looking at the development
of the whole story,

00:38:00.250 --> 00:38:03.650
the girl totally expected
what the guy would say

00:38:03.730 --> 00:38:05.010
when she is here, right?

00:38:05.330 --> 00:38:07.730
So instead of being hurt
by what he says,

00:38:07.890 --> 00:38:10.330
she would prevent him from saying...

00:38:10.490 --> 00:38:13.010
- Please say the line.
- Yes?

00:38:13.210 --> 00:38:14.500
The last line.

00:38:17.620 --> 00:38:18.460
What?

00:38:19.540 --> 00:38:20.780
- Start here.
- Okay.

00:38:21.340 --> 00:38:24.220
If that's also what you think,
l want to--

00:38:24.300 --> 00:38:25.210
No!

00:38:25.290 --> 00:38:27.130
I think you should say it here.

00:38:27.330 --> 00:38:29.560
"I don't want to. lf we'll break up
with a smile,

00:38:29.640 --> 00:38:33.460
l would be a lot happier if we hate
each other to the core!"

00:38:34.500 --> 00:38:35.900
Then cue the music.

00:38:37.060 --> 00:38:38.940
It's a suggestion.
lt isn't absolute.

00:38:39.180 --> 00:38:41.180
There's no correct answer in acting.

00:38:42.060 --> 00:38:44.220
Let's do this again.

00:38:44.580 --> 00:38:46.360
Please let me learn from you.

00:38:48.120 --> 00:38:48.960
Okay!

00:38:49.120 --> 00:38:50.700
Oh, I'm sorry. Please go ahead.

00:38:52.260 --> 00:38:56.820
You're poking your nose
into trouble like this, Ukita?

00:38:56.940 --> 00:39:00.300
Please. This is for a girl
l love like my own daughter.

00:39:01.540 --> 00:39:04.460
I know where he is,

00:39:05.020 --> 00:39:08.700
but won't you be in trouble
if the police sees you two meeting?

00:39:08.820 --> 00:39:11.460
It was years ago. l'll be fine.

00:39:15.920 --> 00:39:18.760
Tell absolutely no one
that l told you where he is.

00:39:18.840 --> 00:39:19.680
Sure.

00:39:19.760 --> 00:39:24.010
"Brothel Paradise"

00:39:25.900 --> 00:39:27.900
"Parking ticket"

00:39:28.180 --> 00:39:29.700
Darn!

00:39:31.940 --> 00:39:33.740
I should've parked it
at the carpark.

00:39:38.700 --> 00:39:40.900
"It is your turn to kill"

00:39:49.740 --> 00:39:52.020
"lt is your turn to kill"

00:39:59.360 --> 00:40:00.400
Good afternoon.

00:40:00.840 --> 00:40:01.840
Good afternoon.

00:40:05.640 --> 00:40:07.160
- Excuse me.
- Yes?

00:40:07.960 --> 00:40:11.680
- Sorry about the other day.
- Don't worry about it.

00:40:12.200 --> 00:40:17.160
I do want to help you,
but l am extremely busy.

00:40:17.800 --> 00:40:19.860
Sure. l understand.

00:40:22.100 --> 00:40:24.040
And one more thing.

00:40:24.920 --> 00:40:25.800
Yes?

00:40:27.560 --> 00:40:29.960
I have information
that will help you,

00:40:30.120 --> 00:40:31.680
that l refrained from telling you.

00:40:32.640 --> 00:40:33.560
Yes?

00:40:34.200 --> 00:40:35.600
It's about Mr Kuzumi.

00:40:36.600 --> 00:40:39.400
I had bumped into him once
at the lift...

00:40:40.840 --> 00:40:42.480
l thought it was fishy,

00:40:42.840 --> 00:40:44.600
so l checked afterwards.

00:40:45.800 --> 00:40:48.080
It had been opened and closed
over and over again.

00:40:49.360 --> 00:40:52.310
Mr Kuzumi probably did this.

00:40:54.710 --> 00:40:57.200
You'd better not trust him too much.

00:41:10.080 --> 00:41:11.720
Sorry to have kept you waiting.

00:41:11.800 --> 00:41:13.040
- It's okay.
- lt's okay.

00:41:16.760 --> 00:41:18.720
I didn't expect...

00:41:19.160 --> 00:41:21.120
lt is messy, isn't it?

00:41:23.040 --> 00:41:24.040
Yeah...

00:41:24.200 --> 00:41:26.400
l've been busy going to school
and work.

00:41:26.520 --> 00:41:28.360
But you have financial support,
right?

00:41:28.520 --> 00:41:31.160
Or you can't rent this flat
on your own.

00:41:31.800 --> 00:41:34.280
Well, my parents own this flat.

00:41:34.520 --> 00:41:36.560
- You made me jealous!
- You made me jealous!

00:41:36.840 --> 00:41:38.520
- We said it together.
- Yeah.

00:41:38.640 --> 00:41:41.720
Well, l've made a summary of
Nana's notes here.

00:41:49.640 --> 00:41:50.600
This is...

00:41:51.200 --> 00:41:53.400
l do maths in university,

00:41:53.560 --> 00:41:56.400
sometimes l can't write
all the calculations in my notebook.

00:42:00.400 --> 00:42:01.760
Wow...

00:42:02.200 --> 00:42:03.560
Our main topic today...

00:42:05.200 --> 00:42:06.200
is this.

00:42:06.400 --> 00:42:11.070
"Game participants,
name written, name drawn"

00:42:11.150 --> 00:42:12.550
"Murderer? Victims"

00:42:12.630 --> 00:42:14.550
"Residents not participating"

00:42:14.790 --> 00:42:15.870
Amazing.

00:42:15.950 --> 00:42:20.430
I somehow feel that some people
don't like what we're doing,

00:42:20.790 --> 00:42:23.150
so l think we'd better
talk here from now on.

00:42:23.990 --> 00:42:25.270
You are right.

00:42:26.230 --> 00:42:29.600
Somehow, l feel that
we can solve the problem.

00:42:33.800 --> 00:42:36.720
"Game participants 101: Kuzumi"

00:42:37.040 --> 00:42:39.400
- Excuse me, Mr Kojima.
- What's the matter?

00:42:39.480 --> 00:42:41.960
I forgot to tell you
that you have a parcel.

00:42:42.040 --> 00:42:42.920
Oh.

00:42:43.080 --> 00:42:45.640
It's bulky and heavy,
so it's at the distribution centre.

00:42:45.800 --> 00:42:48.480
It's fine. That's just my golf bag.

00:42:54.560 --> 00:42:56.200
"But your wife sent it here."

00:43:00.240 --> 00:43:03.910
"Idiot, l don't want to see her,
that's why l made her send it here."

00:43:08.910 --> 00:43:12.230
When l look at this,
everyone seems suspicious.

00:43:13.590 --> 00:43:15.870
Even people who didn't participate
in the game.

00:43:16.110 --> 00:43:19.320
Indeed. Like Room 501's Mr Sano.

00:43:20.280 --> 00:43:24.000
He lives right next to Mrs Akaike.

00:43:24.160 --> 00:43:27.280
But he's been the same as always,
even after the murder.

00:43:27.760 --> 00:43:30.280
He always goes up the stairs
to the fifth floor.

00:43:30.360 --> 00:43:32.320
Yes. lsn't he scary?

00:43:33.120 --> 00:43:35.160
Is Mrs Kojima all right?

00:43:35.480 --> 00:43:37.600
I'm starting to get worried.

00:43:40.200 --> 00:43:42.200
"Staff entrance"

00:43:45.520 --> 00:43:47.040
"Sender: Kayo Kojima"

00:43:55.880 --> 00:43:58.640
Mr Kojima, you must be using
some fine quality clubs.

00:43:58.720 --> 00:44:00.360
- Yeah. You want to see?
- Of course.

00:44:02.120 --> 00:44:03.480
Mrs lshizaki too.

00:44:03.680 --> 00:44:07.550
Mrs lshizaki isn't on her own,
so I'm not worried yet.

00:44:08.350 --> 00:44:13.790
Yeah... Mrs Kojima's husband
hasn't been going home.

00:44:14.590 --> 00:44:16.760
This will surprise
a knowledgeable golf fan.

00:44:18.320 --> 00:44:22.370
But that happened to Mrs Akaike when
all three of them were together.

00:44:24.210 --> 00:44:26.450
Somehow I'm getting worried now.

00:44:27.330 --> 00:44:29.430
Should we go see Mrs Kojima?

00:44:34.260 --> 00:44:35.420
Look!

00:44:35.980 --> 00:44:37.740
Do you know how awesome they are?

00:45:46.210 --> 00:45:49.230
"Your Turn to Kill"

00:45:49.630 --> 00:45:51.390
Who drew my piece of paper?

00:45:51.470 --> 00:45:52.910
We should tell the police.

00:45:52.990 --> 00:45:55.330
The people who threaten us
should be different,

00:45:55.410 --> 00:45:57.490
but the handwriting is the same.

00:45:57.570 --> 00:45:59.610
"Getting close to the truth"
l think someone is lying.

00:45:59.690 --> 00:46:00.530
She was killed.

00:46:00.610 --> 00:46:01.610
You need a motive!

00:46:01.690 --> 00:46:03.890
Nana... l hit the bull's eye!